The paper deals with the cyber-physical security of UAV systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also formulates a game-theoretic model to analyze the interactions between the UAV operator and the interdictor, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also incorporates notions from cumulative prospect theory, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the optimization of UAV path selection, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with the security of time-critical UAV applications, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
